---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Bathroom Tiling Wellington | Rohullah Rassuli Tiling Services"
  description="Expert bathroom tiling in Wellington. Full renovations, shower tiling, waterproofing and more. NZS 4858 compliant. Wellington-wide free quotes — call 021 026 02044."
  canonical="/services/bathroom-tiling"
  serviceName="Bathroom Tiling"
  serviceType="Bathroom Tiling"
  serviceDescription="Professional bathroom tiling services in Wellington including full renovations, shower tiling, waterproofing, and floor-to-ceiling installations."
>

  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split-layout fade-in-up">
        <div>
          <p class="lead">
            A well-tiled bathroom is the centrepiece of any Wellington home. At Rohullah Rassuli Tiling Services, we specialise in bathroom tiling that is not only beautiful but built to last — with proper waterproofing, precise tile placement, and meticulous grouting that protects your home from moisture damage for decades.
          </p>
          <p>
            Whether you are planning a complete bathroom renovation, upgrading an ensuite, or simply refreshing tired wall tiles, we handle every stage of the tiling process. From substrate preparation and waterproofing through to the final grout clean-up, you can trust us to deliver a finish that meets New Zealand building standards and exceeds your expectations.
          </p>
          <p>
            We work with homeowners, builders, and architects throughout the Wellington region — including Lower Hutt, Upper Hutt, Porirua, and the Kāpiti Coast.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--portrait">
            <span>Bathroom tiling project photo</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bathroom Tiling Services -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Bathroom Tiling Services</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">From compact powder rooms to spacious master bathrooms, we deliver expert tiling for every space.</p>

      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Full Bathroom Renovations</h3>
          <p>Complete strip-out and re-tile of walls, floors, and shower areas. We coordinate with plumbers and builders to ensure a seamless renovation from start to finish.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Shower Tiling</h3>
          <p>Precision tiling of shower walls, floors, and niches with full waterproofing. We ensure proper falls to the drain and watertight sealing at every junction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Floor-to-Ceiling Tiling</h3>
          <p>Create a sleek, modern look with tiles running from the floor right up to the ceiling. Ideal for contemporary bathrooms and wet rooms where full waterproofing is required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Ensuite Tiling</h3>
          <p>Make the most of compact ensuite spaces with clever tile layouts, light-reflecting finishes, and space-enhancing patterns that add both style and functionality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Walk-in Showers</h3>
          <p>Open-plan, barrier-free shower areas with precise gradient tiling for proper drainage. A popular choice in Wellington new-builds and accessibility-focused renovations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Vanity Splashbacks</h3>
          <p>Protect the wall behind your vanity with a stylish tiled splashback. Feature tiles, mosaics, or a simple continuation of your main wall tile — the choice is yours.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Materials Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Bathroom Tile Materials</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">We work with a wide range of tile materials to suit your style, budget, and practical requirements.</p>

      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Ceramic Tiles</h3>
          <p>The most popular choice for bathroom walls. Affordable, easy to maintain, and available in thousands of colours, patterns, and sizes. Ideal for splashbacks and feature walls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Porcelain Tiles</h3>
          <p>Denser and more water-resistant than ceramic, porcelain is the go-to for shower floors and wet areas. Extremely durable and available in finishes that replicate natural stone, timber, and concrete.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Mosaic Tiles</h3>
          <p>Small-format tiles on mesh backing, perfect for shower floors, feature strips, and niches. Available in glass, ceramic, porcelain, and natural stone for endless design possibilities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Natural Stone</h3>
          <p>Marble, travertine, slate, and limestone bring organic warmth and luxury to any bathroom. Requires sealing but delivers a timeless, high-end aesthetic that ages beautifully.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Large-Format Tiles</h3>
          <p>Tiles over 600mm create fewer grout lines and a seamless, spacious feel. Popular for modern Wellington bathrooms where a clean, minimalist look is the goal. Requires expert installation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Waterproofing Section -->
  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--white">Waterproofing Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        Waterproofing is not optional in wet areas — it is a legal requirement under the New Zealand Building Code. All bathroom tiling by Rohullah Rassuli Tiling Services includes waterproofing that meets the NZS 4858 standard for wet area membranes.
      </p>
      <p>
        We apply liquid-applied waterproofing membranes to shower walls, floors, and any surface that will be exposed to water. Band reinforcement is used at all internal corners, floor-to-wall junctions, and around penetrations such as shower mixers and waste outlets.
      </p>
      <p>
        When your project requires building consent, we provide <strong>PS3 producer statements</strong> to confirm that waterproofing has been installed in accordance with the manufacturer's specifications and NZS 4858. This documentation is essential for code compliance sign-off in the Wellington region.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/services/waterproofing" class="text-gold">Learn more about our waterproofing services &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our 7-Step Bathroom Tiling Process</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">A proven workflow that delivers consistent, high-quality results on every bathroom project.</p>

      <div class="process-timeline fade-in-up">
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>1. Consultation</h4>
          <p>We visit your property to discuss your vision, review the existing bathroom, and talk through tile options, layout, and budget. This initial consultation is completely free.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>2. Measurement &amp; Quote</h4>
          <p>Precise measurements are taken to calculate tile quantities, adhesive, grout, and waterproofing materials. You receive a detailed, itemised quote with no hidden costs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>3. Surface Preparation</h4>
          <p>Existing tiles are removed (if applicable), and the substrate is inspected, repaired, and levelled. Proper preparation is the foundation of a long-lasting tile installation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>4. Waterproofing</h4>
          <p>Liquid-applied membranes are applied to all wet areas, with band reinforcement at corners and junctions. We allow proper curing time before any tiles are laid.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>5. Tiling</h4>
          <p>Tiles are laid using premium adhesives, with careful attention to layout, spacing, and alignment. We use levelling systems to ensure a perfectly flat finish, especially with large-format tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>6. Grouting &amp; Sealing</h4>
          <p>Grout is applied, cleaned, and sealed where required. Silicone sealant is used at all movement joints, corners, and junctions between tiles and fixtures.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <h4>7. Final Clean-Up &amp; Handover</h4>
          <p>The completed bathroom is thoroughly cleaned, inspected, and handed over to you. We walk you through the finished work and provide care and maintenance advice for your new tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gallery Placeholder -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our Bathroom Tiling Work</h2>
      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Bathroom renovation — Wellington CBD</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Walk-in shower tiling — Lower Hutt</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Ensuite floor-to-ceiling tiles — Whitby</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Internal Links -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--left">Related Services</h2>
      <p>
        Bathroom tiling often goes hand-in-hand with other services we provide. If you are planning a full renovation, you may also need <a href="/services/waterproofing">professional waterproofing</a>, <a href="/services/underfloor-heating">underfloor heating installation</a> beneath your bathroom floor tiles, or <a href="/services/tile-repairs">tile repair and replacement</a> in other areas of your home.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ready to discuss your bathroom tiling project? <a href="/contact">Contact us today</a> for a free, no-obligation quote.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions — Bathroom Tiling</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">How long does a bathroom tiling job take in Wellington?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">A standard bathroom tiling project typically takes 3 to 5 days, depending on the size of the bathroom and complexity of the tile layout. This includes surface preparation, waterproofing, tile installation, and grouting. Larger renovations with custom designs may take up to 7 days.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">Do you waterproof the bathroom before tiling?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">Yes, waterproofing is a critical step in every bathroom tiling project. We apply NZS 4858 compliant waterproofing membranes to all wet areas including showers, floors, and around baths. This protects your home from moisture damage and is required by New Zealand building standards.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">What types of tiles work best for bathrooms?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">Porcelain and ceramic tiles are the most popular choices for Wellington bathrooms due to their durability and water resistance. Large-format porcelain tiles create a modern, spacious feel with fewer grout lines, while mosaic tiles work well for shower floors where extra grip is needed. We can advise on the best options for your space and budget.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">How much does bathroom tiling cost in Wellington?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">Bathroom tiling costs vary depending on the size of the area, tile type, and complexity of the layout. We provide free, no-obligation quotes for every project. Contact us with your bathroom dimensions and tile preferences, and we will give you an honest, transparent price with no hidden costs.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does a bathroom tiling job take in Wellington?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A standard bathroom tiling project typically takes 3 to 5 days, depending on the size of the bathroom and complexity of the tile layout. This includes surface preparation, waterproofing, tile installation, and grouting. Larger renovations with custom designs may take up to 7 days."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you waterproof the bathroom before tiling?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, waterproofing is a critical step in every bathroom tiling project. We apply NZS 4858 compliant waterproofing membranes to all wet areas including showers, floors, and around baths. This protects your home from moisture damage and is required by New Zealand building standards."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What types of tiles work best for bathrooms?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Porcelain and ceramic tiles are the most popular choices for Wellington bathrooms due to their durability and water resistance. Large-format porcelain tiles create a modern, spacious feel with fewer grout lines, while mosaic tiles work well for shower floors where extra grip is needed."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does bathroom tiling cost in Wellington?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Bathroom tiling costs vary depending on the size of the area, tile type, and complexity of the layout. We provide free, no-obligation quotes for every project. Contact us with your bathroom dimensions and tile preferences, and we will give you an honest, transparent price with no hidden costs."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

</ServiceLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in-up').forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>
